      <div class="modal-body">
        <h4>Purpose</h4>
        <p class=""><strong>The main purpose of the Lodge Manager is to manage the lodge in a way that creates a profound guest experience, in line with the service vision and creative concepts of the lodge.</strong></p>

        <p>It is the responsibility of the Lodge Manager to monitor hospitality service, maintenance, gardening and housekeeping standards within the lodge. The role is additionally strategic in nature, and the Lodge Manager must drive the appropriate service directives for the lodges, and move the department towards achieving broader goals.</p>

        <p>In this capacity, guest expectations regarding the standard of service should be exceeded. In addition, the lodges need to be monitored so that they run in a cost effective manner, within the agreed budget.</p>

        <p>The Lodge Manager is also responsible for ensuring that the morale of the lodge staff is kept at a high level, that staff are developed on an ongoing basis and that staff with competencies and skills meeting job requirements are recruited for the department.</p>
        
        <hr>

        <h4>Scope of work</h4>
        <p>In broad terms the Sasakwa Lodge Manager oversees the following key performance areas:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Drive the broader goals of the company, in terms of the lodge, by planning and implementing Strategic Management Plans.</li>
          <li>Management and training of the lodge staff in line with Singita standards.</li>
          <li>Develop staff to ensure successful succession.</li>
          <li>Oversee Sasakwa Lodge & Villa, Serengeti House, Sales Pavillion & Sabayaya at an operational level and ensure that the standards are consistent throughout the lodges and/or departments.</li>
          <li>Ensure the personal attention to guests’ are maintained at the correct standard.</li>
          <li>Maintain the highest standards of housekeeping and maintenance.</li>
          <li>Effective financial management through the administration of orders and effective stock control.</li>
          <li>Effective communication is maintained throughout the lodge and in each department.</li>
          <li>Maintain the design and look of the property as per the standards set out by the design team.</li>
          <li>Adapt and re-invent service standards according to industry demands.</li>
          <li>Bridge the gap between the lodge staff and property operational requirements and the expectations of the management company.</li>
        </ol>

        <hr>

        <h4>As such the person filling this position needs to have:</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>A minimum of an advanced diploma in hospitality management, or a bachelor’s degree in business management, or a minimum of 6 year’s work experience in a well-recognized five star hotel or world class lodge, four of which must be in managerial position.</li>
          <li>A master’s degree or postgraduate diploma will be added advantage.</li>
          <li>Exceptional Food and Beverage knowledge.</li>
          <li>Financial management qualification and/or experience preferable.</li>
          <li>Leadership skills with a qualification and/or experience in communication and/or leadership.</li>
          <li>A hardworking, co-operative manner.</li>
          <li>High standards of service excellence and a passion for the industry.</li>
          <li>Exceptional attention to detail.</li>
          <li>Exceptional English and a second European language would be preferable.</li>
          <li>Good computer literacy and hotel management systems training.</li>
          <li>Excellent management ability.</li>
          <li>A clear understanding of basic labour law and disciplinary procedures.</li>
          <li>A developmental approach to staff.</li>
          <li>Assertiveness, patience and good organizational skills.</li>
          <li>Understanding of housekeeping and maintenance procedures.</li>
          <li>An awareness of developments within the food, bar and lodge industries, as well as international trends in hospitality.</li>
        </ol>

        <p class=""><strong>Highly competitive remuneration package, commensurate with qualifications and experience, will be offered to the successful candidate.</strong></p>
